==Proto-Indo-European==

===Etymology===
The word is either a nominalization of an unattested adjective {{m|ine-pro|*h₂r̥tḱós||destroying}} or a derivative of {{m|ine-pro|*h₂rétḱos|*h₂rétḱ-os ~ *h₂rétḱ-es-|destruction}} (cf. {{cog|ae|𐬭𐬀𐬱𐬀𐬵}}, {{cog|sa|रक्षस्|tr=rákṣas}}).

In late PIE (i.e. post-Anatolian period), the word metathesized into {{m|ine-pro||*h₂ŕ̥ḱtos}} which phonetically surfaced as {{m|ine-pro||*h₂ŕ̥ḱþos}} following the rule that when dental and velar occlusives appear syllable-initially, they metathesize ''tk'' → ''kt'' and turn into a [[w:thorn clusters|thorn cluster]] denoted ''ḱþ''.  See Wikipedia for a discussion of these clusters' makeup.

