==Latin==

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|la|itc-pro|*hēr}}, from {{inh|la|ine-pro|*ǵʰḗr||hedgehog}} (whence also {{cog|grc|χήρ||hedgehog}}), a root noun from {{m|ine-pro|*ǵʰer-||to be excited, be bristly}}, whence also {{cog|grc|χοῖρος||young pig}} and {{cog|sq|derr||pig}} from {{m|ine-pro|*ǵʰóryos|*ǵʰór-yos}}.<ref>{{R:itc:EDL|head=ēr|page=193}}</ref>

====Pronunciation====
* {{la-IPA|ēr}}

====Noun====
{{la-noun|ēr<3>|g=m}}

# [[hedgehog]]

=====Usage notes=====
There is some uncertainty as to the exact forms of this word, especially regarding whether the lemma form of this was ''ēr'' or ''ēris'', as the forms attested in literature could point to either option. Another form, ''irim'' (acc. sing.; found in Plautus, ''Capt.'' 184), seems to be a spelling variant.

=====Declension=====
{{la-ndecl|ēr<3>}}

=====Related terms=====
* {{l|la|ēricius||hedgehog; picket}}

===Etymology 2===

====Pronunciation====
* {{la-IPA}}

====Noun====
{{la-noun|er|g=f|indecl=y}}

# {{non-gloss definition|The name of the letter ''{{l|la|R}}''.}}

=====Usage notes=====
* Multiple Latin names for the letter {{m|la||R}}, {{m|la||r}} have been suggested. The most common is {{m|la||er}} or a [[syllabic]] {{m|la||r}}, although there is some evidence which also supports, as names for the letter, {{m|la||rē}}, {{m|la||rrr}}, {{m|la||ər}}, {{m|la||rə}}, and even (in the fourth- or fifth-century first Antinoë papyrus, which gives Greek transliterations of the Latin names of the Roman alphabet’s letters) {{m|grc|ιρρε}}.

