==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
{{root|grc|ine-pro|*kʷel-}}
Traditionally derived from {{der|grc|ine-pro|*kʷel-||far (in time or space)}}. However, it has been argued (e.g. by Chadwick) that {{cog|gmy|𐀞𐀨𐀍}}, {{l|gmy|𐀞𐀨𐀊||old}} are related, therefore precluding the popularly held etymology with an initial labiovelar.<ref>{{R:gmy:MGV|πάλαι|232}}</ref><ref>{{R:grc:EDG|head=πάλαι|pages=1144–1145}}</ref> Beekes instead compares the Mycenaean to {{m|ine-pro|*pelh₂-}}.

A frozen case-form (perhaps an old dative or fossilized PIE allative), as indicated by the ending {{m|grc||-αι}}; compare {{m|grc|χαμαί}}. See also {{m+|sa|पलित||old, hairy, grey}}.

===Pronunciation===
{{grc-IPA|πά˘λαι}}

===Adverb===
{{head|grc|adverbs}}

# {{lb|grc|of a point in the past}}
