## {{n-g|Of past time closer to the present}}: [[before]], [[earlier]], a while [[ago]]
##* {{Q|grc|Pl.|Cr.|43|b|quote=Σωκράτης: ἄρτι δὲ ἥκεις ἢ '''πάλαι''';<br>Κρίτων: ἐπιεικῶς '''πάλαι'''.|trans=Socrates: Did you arrive just now or '''a while ago'''?<br>Crito: Quite '''a while ago'''.}}
## {{n-g|with a present-tense verb}} since a point in the past, for a long time
##* {{Q|grc|Plato|Meno|93|b|quote=τοῦτ’ ἔστιν ὃ '''πάλαι''' ζητοῦμεν ἐγώ τε καὶ Μένων.|trans=This is what Meno and I have been trying to figure out '''for a while'''.}}

