===Root===
{{ine-root}}<ref>{{R:ine:IEW|volume=III|page=787|head=pā-: pə-}}</ref><ref>{{R:ine:IEW|volume=III|page=839|head=pō(i)-: (pəi- ?:) pī-}}</ref><ref>{{R:ine:LIV|head=*peh₂(i̯)-|page=460}}</ref>

# to [[protect]]
# to [[shepherd]]

====Usage notes====
Semantic shift from "protector" towards "shepherd, herder" can be seen in many branches, signifying the importance of herding. Unusual is the o-grade root in Greek {{m|grc|ποιμήν||shepherd, herdsman}}, where the abstract nomina agentis suffix {{m|ine-pro|*-mn̥}} usually binds e-grade, but that hardly seems sufficient to reconstruct *h₃ in the root and to separate it from {{m|ine-pro||*peh₂-}}.

