===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|cooking|transitive}} To [[cook]] with steam.
#: {{ux|en|The best way to cook artichokes is to '''steam''' them.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To expose to the action of steam; to apply steam to for softening, dressing, or preparing.
#: {{ux|en|to '''steam''' wood or cloth}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To [[produce]] or [[vent]] steam.
#* {{RQ:Dryden The Indian Emperour|36|III|iii|passage=See, ſee, my Brother’s Ghoſt hangs hovering there, / O’re his warm Blood, that '''ſteems''' into the Air, / Revenge, Revenge it cries.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|year=1961|month=February|author=""Balmore""|title=Driving and firing modern French steam locomotives - Part One|journal=Trains Illustrated|page=110|text=I found that the Chapelon '''steamed''' almost too freely, because on a strange locomotive and road one usually tends to overfire a little through a natural lack of confidence.}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To rise in vapour; to issue, or pass off, as vapour.
#: {{ux|en|Our breath '''steamed''' in the cold winter air.}}
#* {{RQ:Boyle Unsuccessfulness of Experiments}}
#*: the dissolved amber was plainly discernable swimming like a thin film upon the surface of the liquor, whence, little by little, it '''steamed''' away into the air.
# {{lb|en|intransitive|figuratively}} To become [[angry]]; to [[fume]]; to be [[incensed]].
# {{lb|en|transitive|figuratively}} To make [[angry]].
#: {{ux|en|It really '''steams''' me to see her treat him like that.}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To be covered with [[condensed]] [[water vapor]].
#: {{ux|en|With all the heavy breathing going on the windows were quickly '''steamed''' in the car.}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To [[travel]] by means of [[steam power]].
#: {{ux|en|We '''steamed''' around the Mediterranean.}}
#: {{ux|en|The ship '''steamed''' out of the harbour.}}
# {{lb|en|figuratively|or|literally}} To [[move]] with great or excessive [[purposefulness]].
#: {{ux|en|If he heard of anyone picking the fruit he would '''steam''' off and lecture them.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en| date=December 29, 2010| author=Chris Whyatt| title=Chelsea 1 - 0 Bolton| work=BBC| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/9309542.stm| passage=That was the hard work largely done as the Ivorian waited for Malouda to '''steam''' into the box before releasing a simple crossed pass which the Frenchman side-footed home with aplomb.}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} To [[exhale]].
#* {{RQ:Spenser Faerie Queene|3|1|passage=like inward fire that outward smoke had '''steemd''' }}

