===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*h₁er-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|erthe}}, from {{inh|en|ang|eorþe}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*erþu}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*erþō||dirt, ground, earth}} (compare {{cog|fy|ierde}}, {{cog|nds|Eerd}}, {{cog|nl|aarde}}, {{cog|nds-nl|eerde}}, {{cog|de|Erde}}, {{cog|da|-}}, {{cog|sv|-}} and {{cog|no|jord}}), related to {{m|gem-pro|*erwô||earth}} (compare {{cog|goh|ero}}, perhaps {{cog|non|jǫrfi}}), from {{der|en|ine-pro|*h₁er-}} (compare {{cog|grc|*ἔρα}} in {{m|grc|ἔραζε||on the ground}}, perhaps {{cog|txb|yare||gravel}}.

Probably unrelated, and of unknown etymology, is {{noncog|xcl|երկիր||earth}}. Likewise, the phonologically similar {{cog|sem-pro|*ʔarṣ́-}}&nbsp;– whence {{noncog|ar|أَرْض}}, {{noncog|he|אֶרֶץ|tr=ʾereṣ}}&nbsp;– is probably not related.

