===Noun===
[[File:BrownSoil.jpg|thumb|Earth or soil ''(sense 1)'']]
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|uncountable}} [[soil|Soil]].
#: {{ux|en|This is good '''earth''' for growing potatoes.}}
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} Any general [[rock]]-based material.
#: {{ux|en|She sighed when the plane's wheels finally touched '''earth'''.}}
# The [[ground]], [[land]] (as opposed to the [[sky]] or [[sea]]).
#: {{ux|en|Birds are of the sky, not of the '''earth'''.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2013-06-07|author=David Simpson
|volume=188|issue=26|page=36|magazine={{w|The Guardian Weekly}}
|title=[http://www.guardian.co.uk/books/2013/may/18/falling-upwards-richard-holmes-review Fantasy of navigation]
|passage=Like most human activities, ballooning has sponsored heroes and hucksters and a good deal in between. For every dedicated scientist patiently recording atmospheric pressure and wind speed while shivering at high altitudes, there is a carnival barker with a bevy of pretty girls willing to dangle from a basket or parachute down to '''earth'''.}}
# {{lb|en|British}} A connection [[electrically]] to the ''earth'' ({{qualifier|US}} [[ground]]); on equipment: a terminal connected in that manner.
# The [[lair]] or [[den]] (as a [[hole]] in the ground) of an animal such as a fox.
# A [[region]] of the planet; a [[land]] or [[country]].
# [[worldly|Worldly]] things, as against spiritual ones.
# The [[world]] of our [[current]] [[life]] (as opposed to [[heaven]] or an [[afterlife]]).
#* {{RQ:Keats Lamia|poem=Ode on a Grecian Urn|stanza=5|page=116|passage="Beauty is truth, truth beauty,"—that is all / Ye know on '''earth''', and all ye need to know.}}
# {{lb|en|metonymically}} The [[people]] on the globe.
#* {{RQ:King James Version|Genesis|11|1|page=87|column=2|passage=And the whole '''earth''' was of one language, and of one [[speach|ſpeach]].}}
# Any [[planet]] similar to the [[Earth]] (our earth): an [[exoplanet]] viewed as another earth, or a potential one. 
#: {{ux|en|New space telescopes may accelerate the search for other '''earths''' that may be out there.}}
# {{lb|en|archaic}} The [[human]] [[body]].
# {{lb|en|alchemy|philosophy|and|Taoism}} The aforementioned soil- or rock-based material, considered one of the {{w|Classical element|four or five classical elements}}.
# {{lb|en|chemistry|obsolete}} Any of certain substances now known to be [[oxide]]s of [[metal]], which were distinguished by being [[infusible]], and by [[insolubility]] in [[water]].

