===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*bʰel- (blow)}}
From {{inh|en|enm|fluid}}, from {{der|en|la|fluidus|t=flowing; fluid}}, from {{der|en|la|fluō|t=to flow}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*bʰleh₁-|t=to swell; surge; overflow; run}}. Akin to {{cog|grc|φλύειν|t=to swell; overflow}}. Not related to {{cog|en|flow}}, which is a native, inherited word from {{m|ine-pro|*plew-}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈfluːɪd/}}
* {{a|obsolete}} {{IPA|en|/ˈfljuːɪd/}}<ref>{{R:Critical Pronouncing Dictionary|entry=Fluid|page=266|ppage=1}}</ref>
