===Etymology 2===
From {{inh|en|enm|stemmen}}, a borrowing from {{der|en|non|stemma|t=to stop, stem, dam}} (whence {{cog|da|stemme}}/{{m|da|stæmme||to stem, dam up}}), from {{der|en|gem-pro|*stammijaną}}. Cognate with {{cog|de|stemmen}}, {{cog|dum|stemmen}}, {{m|dum|stempen}}. Compare {{m|en|stammer}}.

====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[stop]], hinder (for instance, a river or blood).
#: ''to '''stem''' a tide''
#* {{RQ:Denham The Destruction of Troy}}
