==Proto-Uralic==

===Alternative reconstructions===
* {{alter|urj-pro|*witi}}<ref>{{R:urj:RLFD|11}}</ref>

===Etymology===
Possibly connected with {{m+|ine-pro|*wódr̥||water}} and {{m|ine-pro|*wed-}} in some way. Variants of the [[w:Nostratic languages|Nostratic]] and [[w:Indo-Uralic languages|Indo-Uralic]] theories (neither of which is widely accepted) propose common descent, while Koivulehto has proposed that the Uralic term is a borrowing from Indo-European, replacing {{m+|urj-pro|*śäčä}} everywhere but in some of the northern fringes of the family (most prominently {{m+|smi-pro|*čācē}}).<ref>Koivulehto, Jorma. 2002. "The earliest contacts between Indo-European and Uralic speakers in light of lexical loans". In: Carpela, Christian; Parpola, Asko; Koskikallio, Petteri (eds.), ''Early Contacts between Uralic and Indo-European'', pp. 235–263. Suomalais-Ugrilaisen Seuran Toimituksia '''242'''. Helsinki: Suomalais-Ugrilainen Seura.</ref> Aikio however reconstructs the original meaning of {{m|urj-pro||*śäčä}} as "flood",<ref>{{R:Aikio 2016}}</ref> making this less likely. EVE makes no mention of an Indo-European connection for the Uralic word.<ref>{{R:fi:EVE|vesi}}</ref>

