==Finnish==

===Suffix===
{{fi-suffix}}

# {{non-gloss definition|Suffix variant for the illative singular, see {{l|fi|-Vn}}.}}
# {{non-gloss definition|Suffix for the genitive plural. Usually preceded by the plural marker {{l|fi|-i-}} or {{l|fi|-j-}}, but may also have a consonant separator {{l|fi|-d-}} after the plural marker if the words would otherwise have 3 consecutive vowels.}}
# {{lb|fi|personal}} {{non-gloss definition|Forms the impersonal potential present forms of verbs, appended to the infinitive, followed by the potential mood marker {{l|fi|-ne-}}.}}
#: Verbs with a [[consonant stem]] (ending in ''-hda''/''-hdä'', ''-lla''/''-llä'', ''-nna''/''-nnä'', ''-rra''/''-rrä'', ''-sta''/''-stä'', ''-ta''/''-tä'' in the citation form) are followed by ''-ta-'', the mood marker ''-ne-'' and ''-en''.
#:: {{m|fi|juosta}}, consonant stem ''juos-'' + ''-ta-'' + ''-ne-'' + '''''-en''''' → {{m|fi|juostaneen}}
#:: {{m|fi|mennä}}, consonant stem ''men-'' + ''-tä-'' + ''-ne-'' + '''''-en''''' → {{m|fi|mentäneen}}
#:: {{m|fi|nähdä}}, consonant stem ''näh-'' + ''-tä-'' + ''-ne-'' + '''''-en''''' → {{m|fi|nähtäneen}}
#:: {{m|fi|palella}}, consonant stem ''palel-'' + ''-ta-'' + ''-ne-'' + '''''-en''''' → {{m|fi|paleltaneen}}
#:: {{m|fi|haluta}}, consonant stem ''halut-'' + ''-ta-'' + ''-ne-'' + '''''-en''''' → {{m|fi|haluttaneen}}
#: In verbs ending in ''-ea''/''-eä'', ''-oa''/''-öä'', ''-ua''/''-yä'', the verb stem in the weak grade is followed by ''-tta-''/''-ttä'', the mood marker ''-ne-'' and then by this.
#:: {{m|fi|laskea}}, stem ''laske-'' + ''-tta-'' + ''-ne-'' + '''''-en''''' → {{m|fi|laskettaneen}}
#:: {{m|fi|iskeä}}, stem ''iske-'' + ''-ttä-'' + ''-ne-'' + '''''-en''''' → {{m|fi|iskettäneen}}
#:: {{m|fi|sanoa}}, stem ''sano-'' + ''-tta-'' + ''-ne-'' + '''''-en''''' → {{m|fi|sanottaneen}}
#:: {{m|fi|kertoa|ke'''rt'''oa}}, stem ''ker-'' + ''-to- → -'''r'''o-'' + ''-tta'' + '''''-en''''' → {{m|fi|kerrottaneen|ke'''rr'''ottaneen}}
#:: {{m|fi|huolestua}}, stem ''huolestu-'' + ''-tta-'' + ''-ne-'' + '''''-en''''' → {{m|fi|huolestuttaneen}}
#:: {{m|fi|saapua|saa'''p'''ua}}, stem ''saa-'' + ''-pu- → -'''v'''u-'' + ''-tta-'' + ''-ne-'' + '''''-en''''' → {{m|fi|saavuttaneen|saa'''v'''uttaneen}}
#:: {{m|fi|säilöä}}, stem ''säilö-'' + ''-ttä-'' + ''-ne-'' + '''''-en''''' → {{m|fi|säilöttäneen}}
#:: {{m|fi|säilyä}}, stem ''säily-'' + ''-ttä-'' + ''-ne-'' + '''''-en''''' → {{m|fi|säilyttäneen}}
#:: {{m|fi|häipyä|häi'''p'''yä}}, stem ''häi-'' + ''-py- → -'''v'''y-'' + ''-ttä-'' + ''-ne-'' + '''''-en''''' → {{m|fi|häivyttäneen|häi'''v'''yttäneen}}
#: In verbs ending in ''-aa''/''-ää'' or ''-ea''/''-eä'', the beginning stem is followed by ''-etta-'', the mood marker ''-ne-'' and then by this &mdash; consonant gradation occurs.
#:: {{m|fi|paistaa}}, stem ''paist-'' + ''-etta-'' + ''-ne-'' + '''''-en''''' → {{m|fi|paistettaneen}}
#:: {{m|fi|laittaa|lai'''tt'''aa}}, stem ''lait-'' (another ''t'' disappears) + ''-etta-'' + ''-ne-'' + '''''-en''''' → {{m|fi|laitettaneen}}
#:: {{m|fi|vaihtaa|vaih'''t'''aa}}, stem ''vaih-'' + ''-t- → '''-d-''''' + ''-etta-'' + '''''-en-''''' → {{m|fi|vaihdettaneen|vaih'''d'''ettaneen}}
# {{lb|fi|possessive}} {{non-gloss definition|A variant for the third-person possessive suffixes {{l|fi|-nsa}} and {{l|fi|-nsä}}, see the usage notes below.}}

====Usage notes====
* {{q|third-person possessive suffix variant}} When the third-person possessive suffix {{m|fi|-nsa}}/{{m|fi|-nsä}} is appended to nouns that are in singular and plural {{l|en|allative}} and {{l|en|translative}} and plural {{l|en|comitative}}, the ''S'' and ''A''/''Ä'' are very often omitted from the suffix and the last ''E'' of the case suffix preceding the remaining ''N'' is doubled &mdash; resulting in this '''-en'''. In standard Finnish, both the "full" form and the shortened form are acceptable. This same omission takes very often place also in the [[:Category:Finnish long first infinitives|long first infinitives]], used in a shortened sentence expressing "(in order) to do" (see the meanings of {{m|fi|-nsa}} and {{m|fi|-nsä}}):
{{top2}}
:: Singular
: (''allat.'') kirjalle'''nsa''' → kirjalle'''en'''
: (''trans.'') kirjakse'''nsa''' → kirjakse'''en'''
{{mid2}}
:: Plural
: (''allat.'') kirjoille'''nsa''' → kirjoille'''en'''
: (''trans.'') kirjoikse'''nsa''' → kirjoikse'''en'''
: (''comit.'') kirjoine'''nsa''' → kirjoine'''en'''
{{bottom}}

===Anagrams===
* {{anagrams|fi|a=en|-ne|-ne-|ne}}

