# {{non-gloss definition|Replaces the object of a [[causative]] verb.}}

=====Usage notes=====
* ''en'' cannot be used more than once as the object of a given verb.
* While ''en'' is usually used to replace phrases beginning with the preposition {{m|ca|de}}, adverbial phrases (e.g., de {{m|ca|pressa}}) are replaced with {{m|ca|hi}}.
* ''en'' is sometimes used instead of {{m|ca|ho}} to replace an adjective or indefinite noun as the predicate of a verb.
* ''en'' is sometimes used popularly to add emphasis to a sentence: in this sense, it has no translation in English.
