# [[in]] {{gloss|used to describe feelings}}
#: {{ux-lite|fr|inline=1|'''en''' détresse|'''in''' distress}}
# [[in]] {{gloss|as part of something}}
#: {{ux-lite|fr|inline=1|'''en''' équipe|'''on''' a team}}

=====Usage notes=====
* {{m|fr|en|En}} in the sense of ''while'' is often not translated into English.
* When referring to location in countries, provinces, or similar subdivisions in sense 1 and direction in sense 2, {{m|fr|en}} must be used when the name for that very large location is either a feminine singular noun or a vowel-initial masculine singular noun. If the name for the very large location is a consonant-initial masculine singular noun, {{m|fr|au}} is used, while if the name of the very large location is plural, {{m|fr|aux}} is used.

====Further reading====
* {{R:TLFi}}

===Etymology 2===
From {{inh|fr|la|inde|t=thence}}. Compare {{cog|ca|en}}, {{cognate|it|ne|||tr=|pos=|g=|id=}}.

====Pronoun====
{{fr-pron}}

# {{n-g|Used as the object of a verb to indicate an indefinite quantity; [[of]] [[it]], [[of]] [[them]]. Replaces the partitive article (du, de la, etc.)}}
#: {{ux-lite|fr|Essaies-en !|Try some ('''of it / them''')!}}
#: {{ux-lite|fr|Tu as combien de livres ? J''''en''' ai trois.|How many books do you have? I have three ('''of them''').}}
#: {{ux-lite|fr|Y a-t-il beaucoup de pièces ? Oui. Il y '''en''' a beaucoup.|Are there many rooms? Yes, there are many ('''of them''').}}
#: {{ux-lite|fr|Martin a trois sandwichs, mais j''''en''' ai seulement deux.|Martin has three sandwiches, but I have only two ('''of them''').}}
#: {{ux-lite|fr|Il y '''en''' a combien ?|How many '''of them''' are there?}}
#: {{ux-lite|fr|Je bois de l'alcool parce que j''''en''' ai besoin|I drink alcohol because I need ('''of''') '''it'''.}}
#* {{Q|fr|Blaise Pascal|Traité du triangle arithmétique|year=1654|quote=J''''en''' donnerai ici la méthode, que je poursuivrai seulement en deux ou trois exemples, qui seront si aisés à continuer qu'il ne sera pas nécessaire d''''en''' donner davantage.|trans=I shall give ('''of it''') here the method that I shall pursue only in two or three examples, which will be so easy to continue that it will not be necessary to give more '''of them'''.}}
# {{n-g|Adverbial preposition indicating movement away from a place already mentioned; [[from]] [[there]], [[from]] [[it]]. Replaces the phrase ''de là'' or ''d’ici''.}}
#: {{ux-lite|fr|Est-ce qu'elle vient de Barcelone ? Oui, elle '''en''' vient.|Does she come from Barcelona? Yes, she comes ('''from there''').}}

