==Finnish==

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|fi|fiu-fin-pro|*-n}}, from {{inh|fi|urj-pro|*-n|pos=genitive suffix}}.

====Suffix====
{{fi-suffix|case}}

# {{n-g|Used to form the [[genitive]] case.}}
#: [[tyttö|tytö]]'''n''' takki "a girl's coat"
#: [[poika]]'''n'''[[-ni|i]] takki "the coat of my son"

=====Usage notes=====
* When [[possessive suffix]]es are used, the genitive doesn't have its suffix '''-n'''. The possessive suffixes are appended to a vowel stem instead, thus rendering the nominative and genitive singular identical.

===Etymology 2===
From {{inh|fi|fiu-fin-pro|*-n}}, from {{inh|fi|urj-pro|*-m||accusative suffix}}.

====Suffix====
{{fi-suffix|case}}

# {{n-g|Used to form the [[accusative]] case.}}
#: {{ux|fi|Näin tytö'''n'''.|I saw ''a/the girl''.}}
#: {{ux|fi|Tapasin poika'''n'''i eilen.|I met my ''son'' yesterday.}}

=====Usage notes=====
* The genitive singular and accusative singular look coincidentally identical in Finnish. The [[object]] of a transitive verb may look also like the [[nominative]] but it's still called the accusative in traditional grammars. There's also the partial object, which uses the [[partitive]] case. For the accusative forms of personal pronouns and the interrogative pronoun ''[[ken]]'', see [[-t#Finnish|-t]].

===Etymology 3===
From {{inh|fi|fiu-fin-pro|*-n}}, from {{inh|fi|urj-pro|*-n}}.

====Suffix====
{{fi-suffix|case}}

# {{n-g|Used to form the [[instructive]] case, usually only in the plural.}}
#: ''Pääsin ojan yli '''kuivin''' '''jaloin''''' "I could cross the ditch with dry feet."

=====Usage notes=====
* The only occasion where this suffix is used with a possessive suffix &mdash; without being to be translated &mdash; is the idiom ''[[käydä]] [[pää|päi]]'''n'''[[-nsä|sä]]'' "to be acceptable" (the plural stem ''päi-'' of the noun ''[[pää]]'' and the suffix ''[[-nsä]]'').

===Etymology 4===
From {{inh|fi|fiu-fin-pro|*-n}}, from {{inh|fi|urj-pro|-}} first-person singular suffix ''*-mV'', probably connected with the first person pronoun ''*mV''; see {{m|fi|minä}}.

====Suffix====
