==Old Norse==

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|non|gmq-pro|*-īna-|sc=Latn}}, from {{inh|non|gem-pro|*-īnaz}}, from {{inh|non|ine-pro|*-iHnos}}.
Originally, this suffix was used to create adjectives that refer to materials, such as Old Norse {{m|non|eikinn||[[oaken]]}}, from {{m|non|eik||oak}} and {{m|non|gullinn||[[golden]]}}, from {{m|non|gull||gold}}.
Later, use of this suffix was extended to create adjectives from verbs, such as Old Norse {{m|non|lyginn||prone to lying}}, from {{m|non|ljúga||to lie}}.<ref>Ragnvald Iversen, ''Norrøn grammatikk'', sjette rev. utg. 1961; p. 208</ref>

