===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|trewe}}, from {{inh|en|ang|trīewe}}, (Mercian) {{m|ang|trēowe||trusty, faithful}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*triwwiz}} (compare {{cog|stq|trjou||honest}}, {{cog|nl|getrouw}} and {{m|nl|trouw}}, {{cog|de|treu}}, {{cog|no|-}} and {{cog|sv|trygg||safe, secure’}}, from pre-Germanic *''drewh₂yos'', from {{der|en|ine-pro|*drewh₂-||steady, firm}} (compare {{cog|ga|dearbh||sure}}, {{cog|prg|druwis||faith}}, {{cog|grc|δροόν||firm}}), extension of {{m|ine-pro|*dóru||tree}}. More at {{m|en|tree}}.

For the semantic development, compare {{cog|la|robustus||tough}} from {{m|la|robur||red oak}}.

