===Etymology===
From two sources, both reflecting earlier {{m|gem-pro||*-ōjaną}}:
* From {{inh|gem-pro|ine-pro|*-eh₂yéti}}, an innovated compound suffix from {{m|ine-pro|*-éh₂|pos=eh₂-stem noun suffix}} + {{m|ine-pro|*-yéti|pos=denominative suffix}}. These were originally formed as denominative verbs from ō-stem nouns. When attached to {{l|en|thematic}} (a-stem) nouns, the thematic vowel was also retained, but the resulting compound suffix {{m|ine-pro||*-eyé-}} became part of the first weak class instead.
* From {{inh|gem-pro|ine-pro|*-h₂yéti|*-(e)h₂yéti}}, an innovated compound suffix from {{m|ine-pro|*-h₂ti|*-(e)h₂ti|pos=factitive verb suffix}} which was originally athematic, but later extended with the thematic present suffix {{m|ine-pro|*-yéti}}.
Cognates include {{cog|la|-āre|pos=first conjugation}}, {{cog|grc|-άω|pos=contracted verb}}, {{cog|sa|-आयति|tr=-ā́yati}}.

