# {{lb|en|intransitive|followed by '''on''' or '''upon'''}} To [[concentrate]] during a [[task]].
#: {{ux|en|I have to '''focus''' on my work.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To direct attention, effort, or energy to a particular audience or task.
#: {{ux|en|The president '''focused''' her remarks to the newcomers.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To cause ([[ray]]s of [[light]], etc) to converge at a single point.
#* {{quote-journal|en|year=1961|month=February|title=Talking of Trains: Collision at Newcastle|journal=Trains Illustrated|pages=75-76|text=The difficulties of '''focussing''' colour-light signals on curved tracks to ensure maximum sighting distance were underlined in the recent official report [...] on a low-speed collision at Newcastle Central on July 25, 1960, between an unfitted freight and a diesel-hauled passenger train.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[adjust]] (a [[lens]], an optical instrument) in order to position an image with respect to the [[focal plane]].
#: ''You'll need to '''focus''' the microscope carefully in order to capture the full detail of this surface.''
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To [[concentrate]] one’s [[attention]].
#: ''If you're going to beat your competitors, you need to '''focus'''.''
# {{lb|en|computing|GUI|transitive}} To transfer the [[input]] focus to (a visual element), so that it receives subsequent input.
#: ''The text box won't receive the user's keystrokes unless you explicitly '''focus''' it.''
# {{lb|en|accounting|formerly}} To [[aggregate]] figures of accounts.
#* {{quote-book|1=en|year=1897|author=Bram Stoker|authorlink=Bram Stoker|title=Dracula|year_published=1993|page=67|passage=Whole pages of it are filled with masses of figures, generally single numbers added up in batches, and then the totals added in batches again, as though he were "'''focusing'''" some account, as the auditors put it.}}

====Usage notes====
The spellings ''focusses'', ''focussing'', ''focussed'' are more common in Commonwealth English than in American English, but in both varieties they are less common than the spellings ''focuses'', ''focusing'', ''focused''.

