==Latin==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|la|itc-pro|*fuiō}}, ultimately from {{inh|la|ine-pro|*bʰuH-||to grow, become, come into being, appear}}. Compare with {{m|la|fuī}}, originally the perfect of this verb but now attached to {{m|la|sum||I am}}; and constructions with {{m|la|-bō}}, {{m|la|-bam}} (e.g. {{m|la|amābō}}, {{m|la|placēbō}}, {{m|la|nocēbō}}, {{m|la|monēbam}}, {{m|la|audiēbam}}).

The past participle is that of the unrelated verb {{m|la|faciō||I make, do}}. In Latin ''faciō'' and ''fīō'' were treated as the [[active]] and [[passive]] equivalents of each other, an example of [[suppletion]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{la-IPA|fīō}}

Note: the i in fi- is pronounced long, except when it is followed by er or en.

===Verb===
{{la-verb|irreg|fīō}}

# {{lb|la|passive form of}} {{l|la|faciō}}
# {{lb|la|copulative}} I [[become]], am [[made]]
#: {{uxi|la|Vōs ōrāmus ut discipulī ācerrimī '''fīātis'''|t=We are begging you so that '''you may become''' very keen students}}
# I [[happen]], [[take place]], [[result]], [[arise]]
#: {{syn|la|interveniō|ēveniō|expetō|obtingō|incurrō|accēdō|incidō|accidō|intercidō|contingō}}
#: {{uxi|la|{{l|la|ut}} '''fit'''|t=as '''happens''' usually/as is customary}}
#: {{uxi|la|'''fit''' {{l|la|ut}}|t=it '''happens''' that}}
#* {{Q|la|[[w:Titus Livius|Titus Livius]]|[[w:Ab Urbe Condita Libri|Ab Urbe Condita]]|I, 13|quote={{l|la|silentium}} {{l|la|et}} {{l|la|repentina}}  '''fit''' {{l|la|quies}}|t=A stillness and a sudden hush '''took place'''}}
# I [[appear]]
#* {{Q|la|[[w:Titus Livius|Titus Livius]]|[[w:Ab Urbe Condita Libri|Ab Urbe Condita]]|I, 10|quote='''fit''' {{l|la|obvius}} {{l|la|cum}} {{l|la|exercitus|exercitu}} [[w:Romulus|Romulus]]|t=Romulus '''appeared''' with his army}}

====Conjugation====
While it does have a fourth conjugation pattern when conjugated, this verb has an irregular infinitive (fierī), and is therefore third conjugation.
