#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2013-06-07|author=David Simpson|volume=188|issue=26|page=36|magazine={{w|The Guardian Weekly}}|title=Fantasy of navigation|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/books/2013/may/18/falling-upwards-richard-holmes-review|passage=Like most human activities, ballooning has sponsored heroes and hucksters and a good '''deal''' in between. For every dedicated scientist patiently recording atmospheric pressure and wind speed while shivering at high altitudes, there is a carnival barker with a bevy of pretty girls willing to dangle from a basket or parachute down to earth.}}

