#* {{quote-book|en|year=1819|title=Practical abridgement of the laws of customs and excise|author=Charles Pope|edition=5th|page=CCXLIII|passage=It shall not be lawful for any person to land any timber, planks or board, '''deals''', staves, tar, pitch, turpentine, rozin or other the commodities aforesaid, on any part of the present quays within the city of Bristol, from any vessel coming into the said port...}}
