===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|countable}} [[form|Form]] created in the [[mind]], rather than the forms [[perceived]] through the five [[sense]]s; an [[instance]] of [[think]]ing.
#: {{ux|en|The greatest weapon against stress is our ability to choose one '''thought''' over another.}}
#* {{RQ:Churchill Celebrity|chapter=8|passage=I corralled the judge, and we started off across the fields, in no very mild state of fear of that gentleman's wife, whose vigilance was seldom relaxed. And thus we came by a circuitous route to Mohair, the judge occupied by his own guilty '''thoughts''', and I by others not less disturbing.}}
#* {{RQ:Maxwell Mirror and the Lamp|chapter=5|passage=He was thinking; but the glory of the song, the swell from the great organ, the clustered lights, {{...}}, the height and vastness of this noble fane, its antiquity and its strength—all these things seemed to have their part as causes of the thrilling emotion that accompanied his '''thoughts'''.}}
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} The [[operation]] by which such forms [[arise]] or are [[manipulated]]; the [[process]] of [[think]]ing; the [[agency]] by which [[think]]ing is [[accomplish]]ed.
#: {{ux|en|Without freedom of '''thought''' there can be no such thing as wisdom, and no such thing as public liberty without freedom of speech.}}
#* ''a. 1983''', {{w|Paul Fix}} (attributed quote)
#*: The only reason some people get lost in '''thought''' is because it’s unfamiliar territory.
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} A [[way]] of thinking (associated with a [[group]], [[nation]] or [[region]]).
#: {{ux|en|Traditional eastern '''thought''' differs markedly from that of the west.}}
# {{lb|en|uncountable|now|dialectal}} [[anxiety|Anxiety]], [[distress]].
#* {{RQ:King James Version|Matthew|6|27|passage=Which of you by taking '''thought''', can adde one cubite vnto his ſtature?}}
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} The careful [[consideration]] of multiple factors; [[deliberation]].
#: {{syn|en|Thesaurus:consideration}}
#: {{ux|en|After much thought, I have decided to stay.}}
# A very small amount, distance, etc.; a [[whit]] or [[jot]].
#* '''1902''', John Buchan, ''The Outgoing of the Tide''
#*: 'Bide the night at Heriotside,' says he. 'It's a '''thought''' out of your way, but it's a comfortable bit.'

